# A former state, landlocked in south-central India, which was ruled from 1724 until 1948 by a line of [[nizam]]s.
#* '''2008''', ''Britannica Concise Encyclopedia'' (ISBN 1593394926), page 916:
#*: At Indian partition in 1947, the nizam chose to resume '''Hyderabad's''' independent status, but India invaded the state (1948) and took control.
